overview: The user initiated a request for a complete aesthetic overhaul of
  their sleep questionnaire application, aiming to transform its "okay" but
  generic appearance into something more visually appealing and professional.
  The agent began by thoroughly reviewing the existing CSS and component files
  to understand the current design language. A detailed plan was then formulated
  to address issues such as the generic color palette, plain backgrounds, dense
  form sections, and lack of visual personality. The implementation involved
  introducing a calming, sleep-themed color palette with deep indigos, purples,
  and teal accents. Key UI components like the main form layout, progress bar,
  welcome screen, checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders were redesigned with
  softer aesthetics, subtle gradients, and improved visual feedback. The report
  section also received a significant facelift to align with the new theme. The
  agent confirmed successful compilation of all changes and proceeded to a
  visual inspection in the browser to ensure the desired "beautiful" outcome was
  achieved.
